14-11-23 }}</ref> \n|-\\\n!Nationality || Numbers || % of total<br />(% of foreigners)\n|-\n||{{flag|Germany}}|| 14,093 || 3.6 (20.0)\n|-\n||{{flag|Italy}} || 7,147 || 1.8 (10.1)\n|-\n||{{flag|Portugal}}|| 7,063 || 1.8 (10.0)\n|-\n||{{flag|Kosovo}}|| 6,641 || 1.7 (9.4)\n|-\n||{{flag|Serbia}}|| 5,986 || 1.5 (8.5)\n|-\n||{{flag|Republic of Macedonia}}|| 2,299 || 0.6 (3.3)\n|-\n||{{flag|Croatia}}|| 2,203 || 0.6 (3.1)\n|-\n||{{flag|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}|| 2,137 || 0.5 (3.0)\n|-\n||{{flag|Spain}}|| 2,037 || 0.5 (2.9)\n|-\n||{{flag|Turkey}}|| 1,624 || 0.4 (2.3)\n|-\n||{{flag|Austria}}|| 1,567 || 0.4 (2.2)\n|-\n||{{flag|Sri Lanka}}|| 1,477 || 0.4 (2.1)\n|}\n\nLucerne has a population ({{as of|{{Swiss populations YM|CH-LU}}|lc=on}}) of {{Swiss populations|CH-LU|CH-LU}}.{{Swiss populations ref|CH-LU}}  {{as of|2013}}, 18.1% of the population are resident foreign nationals, of which 15.5% are from [[Europe]], 1.4% from [[Asia]], 0.7% from [[Africa]], and 0.5% from [[Americas|America]].<ref name=Lustat2013/> Over the last 10 years (2000\u20132010) the population has changed at a rate of \u22120.4%. Migration accounted for \u22121.2%, while births and deaths accounted for 1.3%.<ref name=SFSO>[http://www.bfs.admin.ch/bfs/portal/en/index/regionen/regionalportraets.html Swiss Federal Statistical Office] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115203755/http://www.bfs.admin.ch/bfs/portal/en/index/regionen/regionalportraets.html |date=15 January 2012 }}. Retrieved 17 January 2012</ref>\n\nMost of the population ({{as of|2010|lc=on}}) speaks [[German language|German]] (91%) as their first language, while [[Serbo-Croatian]], [[Italian Language|Italian]], [[Albanian language|Albanian]] and [[English Language|English]] are the second most common languages (3%), followed by [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] and [[French language|French]] with 2% each, and [[Spanish language|Spanish]] with 1%.<ref name=Lustat2010Lang>{{cite web |title=Wohnbev\u00f6lkerung nach Hauptsprachen seit 2010 - Kanton Luzern |url=http://www2.lustat.ch/download/lustat_new/kt/0003/w163_005t_kt0003_zz_d_0000_002.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20141123185532/http://www2.lustat.ch/download/lustat_new/kt/0003/w163_005t_kt0003_zz_d_0000_002.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=23 November 2014 |publisher=lustat - Statistik Luzern, Kanton Luzern |date=10 March 2014 |type=Database excerpt |website=www.lustat.ch |language=German |accessdate=2014-11-23 }}</ref>\n\nOf the population in the canton, 115,233 or about 32.9% were born in Lucerne and lived there in 2000.  There were 101,980 or 29.1% who were born in the same canton, while 66,486 or 19.0% were born somewhere else in Switzerland, and 55,314 or 15.8% were born outside of Switzerland.<ref name=STAT2000/>  {{as of|2000}}, children and teenagers (0\u201319 years old) make up 25% of the population, while adults (20\u201364 years old) make up 58.6% and seniors (over 64 years old) make up 16.4%.<ref name=SFSO/>\n\n{{as of|2000}}, there were 158,345 people who were single and never married in the canton.  There were 159,152 married individuals, 18,853 widows or widowers and 14,154 individuals who are divorced.<ref name=STAT2000>[http://www.pxweb.bfs.admin.ch/Database/German_40%20-%20Eidgen%C3%B6ssische%20Volksz%C3%A4hlung/40.3%20-%202000/40.3%20-%202000.asp?lang=1&prod=40&secprod=3&openChild=true STAT-TAB Datenw\u00fcrfel f\u00fcr Thema 40.3 \u2013 2000] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409212530/http://www.pxweb.bfs.admin.ch/Database/German_40%20-%20Eidgen%C3%B6ssische%20Volksz%C3%A4hlung/40.3%20-%202000/40.3%20-%202000.asp?lang=1&prod=40&secprod=3&openChild=true |date=9 April 2014 }}  {{in lang|de}}. Retrieved 2 February 2011</ref>\n\n{{as of|2000}}, there were 13,430 private households in the canton, and an average of 2.5 persons per household.<ref name=SFSO/>  There were 47,012 households that consist of only one person and 12,952 households with five or more people.  {{as of|2009}}, the construction rate of new housing units was 4.7 new units per 1000 residents.<ref name=SFSO/>\n\n{{as of|2003}} the average price to rent an average apartment in Lucerne city was 1150.31 [[Swiss franc]]s (CHF) per month (US$920, \u00a3520, \u20ac740 approx. exchange rate from 2003).  The average rate for a one-room apartment was 646.07 CHF (US$520, \u00a3290, \u20ac410), a two-room apartment was about 879.64 CHF (US$700, \u00a3400, \u20ac560), a three-room apartment was about 1033.60 CHF (US$830, \u00a3470, \u20ac660) and a six or more room apartment cost an average of 2032.38 CHF (US$1630, \u00a3910, \u20ac1300).  The average apartment price in Lucerne was 103.1% of the national average of 1116 CHF.<ref name=BFS_rent>[http://www.bfs.admin.ch/bfs/portal/de/index/themen/05/06/blank/key/einfuehrung.html Swiss Federal Statistical Office-Rental prices] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100423161803/http://www.bfs.admin.ch/bfs/portal/de/index/themen/05/06/blank/key/einfuehrung.html |date=23 April 2010 }} 2003 data {{in lang|de}}. Retrieved 26 May 2010</ref>  The vacancy rate for the canton, {{as of|2010|alt=in 2010}}, was 0.77%.<ref name=SFSO/>\n\nThe largest population centres are [[Lucerne]], [[Emmen, Switzerland|Emmen]] and [[Kriens]].\n\n===Historic population===\n\nThe historical population is given in the following chart:<ref name=HDS>{{HDS|2973|Lucerne}}</ref>\n<timeline>\nColors=\n  id:lightgrey value:gray(0.9)\n  id:darkgrey  value:gray(0.8)\nImageSize  = width:800 height:500\nPlotArea   = top:10 left: 100 bottom:90 right:100\nLegend     = columns:3 left:220 top:70 columnwidth:160\nAlignBars  = justify\nDateFormat = x.y\nPeriod     = from:0 till:360000\nTimeAxis   = orientation:vertical\nAlignBars  = justify\nScaleMajor = gridcolor:darkgrey increment:70000 start:0\nScaleMinor = gridcolor:lightgrey increment:14000 start:0\nColors=\n id:TO     value:yellowgreen      legend:Total\n id:GE     value:teal      legend:German_Speaking\n id:IT     value:green    