 goods.\n\nTourism is of great importance. The canton of Lucerne is a gateway to holiday resorts in the nearby Alps, and much of the transit traffic between Germany and [[Italy]] crosses the region.\n\n{{as of|2010|In 2010}}, Luzern had an unemployment rate of 1.4%.  {{as of|2008}}, there were 1,764 people employed in the [[Primary sector of the economy|primary economic sector]] and about 703 businesses involved in this sector.  5,388 people were employed in the [[Secondary sector of the economy|secondary sector]] and there were 324 businesses in this sector.  9,431 people were employed in the [[Tertiary sector of the economy|tertiary sector]], with 1,113 businesses in this sector.<ref name=SFSO/>\n\n{{as of|2008|alt=In 2008}} the total number of [[full-time equivalent]] jobs was 160,133.  The number of jobs in the primary sector was 9,608, of which 9,462 were in agriculture, 119 were in forestry or lumber production and 27 were in fishing or fisheries.  The number of jobs in the secondary sector was 48,191 of which 31,698 or (65.8%) were in manufacturing, 142 or (0.3%) were in mining and 14,990 (31.1%) were in construction.  The number of jobs in the tertiary sector was 102,334.  In the tertiary sector; 25,105 or 24.5% were in the sale or repair of motor vehicles, 8,182 or 8.0% were in the movement and storage of goods, 8,146 or 8.0% were in a hotel or restaurant, 3,835 or 3.7% were in the information industry, 7,000 or 6.8% were the insurance or financial industry, 10,979 or 10.7% were technical professionals or scientists, 8,111 or 7.9% were in education and 15,924 or 15.6% were in health care.<ref>[http://www.pxweb.bfs.admin.ch/Database/German_06%20-%20Industrie%20und%20Dienstleistungen/06.2%20-%20Unternehmen/06.2%20-%20Unternehmen.asp?lang=1&prod=06&secprod=2&openChild=true Swiss Federal Statistical Office STAT-TAB Betriebsz\u00e4hlung: Arbeitsst\u00e4tten nach Gemeinde und NOGA 2008 (Abschnitte), Sektoren 1\u20133] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141225013454/http://www.pxweb.bfs.admin.ch/Database/German_06%20-%20Industrie%20und%20Dienstleistungen/06.2%20-%20Unternehmen/06.2%20-%20Unternehmen.asp?lang=1&prod=06&secprod=2&openChild=true |date=25 December 2014 }} {{in lang|de}}. Retrieved 28 January 2011</ref>\n\nOf the working population, 12.1% used public transportation to get to work, and 48.5% used a private car.<ref name=SFSO/>\n\n==Religion==\nFrom the {{as of|2000|alt=2000 census}}, 248,545 or 70.9% were Roman Catholic, while 39,426 or 11.2% belonged to the [[Swiss Reformed Church]].  Of the rest of the population, there were 7,801 [[Orthodox Christianity|members of an Orthodox church]] (or 2.23% of the population), there were 471 individuals (or 0.13% of the population) who belonged to the [[Christian Catholic Church of Switzerland|Christian Catholic Church]], and there were 7,564 individuals (or 2.16% of the population) who belonged to another Christian church.  There were 399 individuals (or 0.11% of the population) who were Jewish, and 13,227 (or 3.77% of the population) who were Islamic.  There were 875 individuals who were [[Buddhism|Buddhist]], 1,715 individuals who were [[Hinduism|Hindu]] and 293 individuals who belonged to another church.  20,681 (or 5.90% of the population) belonged to no church, are agnostic or [[Atheism|atheist]], and 13,007 individuals (or 3.71% of the population) did not answer the question.<ref name=STAT2000/>\n\n==Education==\nIn [[Luzern]] about 127,331 or (36.3%) of the population have completed non-mandatory [[Education in Switzerland#Secondary|upper secondary education]], and 42,391 or (12.1%) have completed additional [[higher education]] (either [[List of universities in Switzerland|universities]] or a ''[[Fachhochschule]]'').  Of the 42,391 who completed tertiary schooling, 65.0% were Swiss men, 23.6% were Swiss women, 7.0% were non-Swiss men and 4.4% were non-Swiss women.<ref name=STAT2000/>\n\nInstitutions of [[higher education]] include the [[Lucerne University of Applied Sciences]] which also has campuses in [[Lucerne]] and [[Horw]].\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.lu.ch/ Official Site] {{in lang|de}}\n*[http://www.staatsarchiv.lu.ch/index/english.htm Public Records Office / State Archive] {{in lang|de}}\n*[http://www.bfs.admin.ch/bfs/portal/en/index/regionen/kantone/lu/key.html Official Statistics]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070421220157/http://www.rawi.lu.ch/geoinformation_vermessung/geoportal.htm Geoportal] {{in lang|de}} GIS\n*{{HDS|7382}}\n\n{{Cantons of Switzerland}}\n{{Portal bar|Switzerland}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lucerne}}\n[[Category:Canton of Lucerne| ]]\n[[Category:Cantons of Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Cantons of the Helvetic Republic]]\n", "name_user": "WOSlinker", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix bold", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canton_of_Lucerne"}
{"title_page": "Drone display", "text_new": "[[File:Intel-Drone-100-Light-Show-980x653.jpg|thumb|\"Drone100\" performed by Ars Electronica Futurelab, for Intel, in 2015]]\nA '''drone display''' is the use of multiple [[unmanned aerial vehicle]]s (drones), often [[quadcopters]], flying in a coordinated fashion for public display. They are usually equipped with [[LED]]s, and the display held at night. The first Drone Display was presented in 2012 in Linz/Austria, where the Ars Electronica Futurelab introduced [[Ars Electronica#SPAXELS|Spaxels]] for the first time. The displays may be for entertainment, where the drones may use [[Flocking (behavior)|flocking]] or [[Swarm robotics|swarming behaviour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/studio-drift-franchise-freedom-smart-creativity/index.html|title=Swarm of drones illuminates the night sky|date=17 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref> The drones may also be coordinated to produce images. Using this [[emerging technology]], displays have been employed for advertising purposes as well.\n\n[[Intel]] has produced the [[Shooting Star (drone)|Shooting Star]], a type of drone used in light shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newsroom.intel.com/news/intel-celebrates-lgbtq-pride-2018-drone-light-show/|title=Intel Celebrates LGBTQ Pride 2018 with Drone Light Show - Intel Newsroom|publisher=}}</ref> They were used during the 2018 Winter Olympics, a Super Bowl halftime show in 2017, and a 2018 4 July celebration.<ref name=\"wired.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/story/more-inclusive-fourth-of-july-drone-show/|title=A Fourth of July Drone Show Helps Military Families With Special Needs|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nDrone light shows differ from fireworks displays in that drones are reusable, and do not produce air and noise pollution.<ref name=\"wired.com\"/> However, drone displays cannot take place during rain or strong winds.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/local/wisconsin/2018/07/27/drone-light-show-lights-up-evening-air-show-oshkosh/845104002/|title=Lighted drone show sparkles and wows crowd at EAA AirVenture|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==List of drone displays==\n*September 2012 - 49 LED-Equipped UAVs, called [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] (short for \"Space Elements\") have been shown at this [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ShGl5rQK3ew&list=PLKrmQr-thTw5kB1sqiEf4_XihIGfbB8XG&index=11 world premiere] by [[Ars Electronica]] [https://ars.electronica.art/futurelab/en/ Futurelab]\n*March 2013 - 50 [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] have been used to perform the Movie Premiere \"Startrek, Into Darkness\" next to Tower Bridge in London.\n*August 2013 - 30 [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] have been used to perform the [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NCOubOVh-yg&list=PLKrmQr-thTw5kB1sqiEf4_XihIGfbB8XG&index=12 opening of the new campus] at QUT, Brisbane / Australia.\n*November 2015 - 100 [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] were used for the first [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]] [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nTwX1Z68qMY&list=PLKrmQr-thTw5kB1sqiEf4_XihIGfbB8XG&index=4 \"Drone100\"] by Ars Electronica Futurelab for Intel.  \n*November 2016 - Five hundred drones were used in Krailling, Germany, a [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]].\n*2017 - Three hundred drones performed during a [[Lady Gaga]] song in the [[Super Bowl LI halftime show]].\n*2017 - At the Fortune Global Forum in China, 1,180 drones performed.\n*September 2017 - To mark the release of the home version of the Wonder Woman film, 300 drones displayed an enormous \"W\" in the night sky above Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/tech/2017/09/19/drones-put-on-stunning-wonder-woman-display.html|title=Drones put on stunning 'Wonder Woman' display|first=Chris|last=Ciaccia|date=19 September 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n*December 2017 -  A swarm of 300 drones performed at [[Art Basel]] in [[Miami Beach]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nltimes.nl/2017/12/14/dutch-artists-fly-300-drone-starlings-swarm-miami|title=Dutch artists fly 300-drone \"starlings\" swarm in Miami|date=14 December 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n*2018 - During the [[2018 Winter Olympics opening ceremony]], 1,218 drones performed, breaking the previous world record.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/olympics-opening-ceremony-drone-show/|title=Inside the Olympics Opening Ceremony World-Record Drone Show|work=WIRED|access-date=2018-02-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n*June 2018 - One hundred drones performed in [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]], England, making shapes to music at the opening of the Great Exhibition of the North.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dezeen.com/2018/06/30/swarm-drones-perform-opening-great-exhibition-north-technology/ |title=Swarm of drones perform at the opening of the Great Exhibition of the North |publisher=Dezeen.com |date=2018-06-30 |accessdate=2018-09-18}}</ref>\n*July 2018 - Intel celebrates 50th anniversary with 2018 simultaneous drones over facility in Folsom, California, for Guinness world record.<ref>{{cite web |title=Intel Breaks Guinness World Records Title for Drone Light Shows in Celebration of 50th Anniversary |url=https://newsroom.intel.com/news/intel-breaks-guinness-world-records-title-drone-light-shows-celebration-50th-anniversary |website=News Byte |publisher=Intel Corporation |accessdate=August 2, 2019}}</ref>  Guinness credited Intel with flying 2066 simultaneous drones.<ref>{{cite web |title=Most Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs) airborne simultaneously |url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/373319-most%C2%A0unmanned-aerial%C2%A0vehicles%C2%A0uavs-airborne%C2%A0simultaneously%C2%A05-kg-or-less/ |website=Guinness World Records |publisher=Guinness World Records Limited |accessdate=August 2, 2019}}</ref>\n*January 2019 - Two hundred drones deployed the World's first New Year's Countdown set to fireworks and music for the New Year Celebrations on Al Marjan Island.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://skymagic.show/journal/al-marjan-island/|title=New Year Drone Show Celebrations|first=Emily|last=Wallace|date=28 February 2019|publisher=Skymagic}}</ref>\n*July 2019 - Two hundred and fifty drones performed at the opening show of the 24th World Scout Jamboree.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.2019wsj.org/opening-ceremony-drones/|title=Opening Ceremony Drones|date=29 July 2019|publisher=New World 19, LLC}}</ref>\n*August 2019 - Five hundred drones performed at the 80 years of VDNH celebration in Moscow<ref>https://www.1tv.ru/news/2019-08-04/369828-potryasayuschey_krasoty_shou_dronov_proshlo_na_vdnh_v_chest_80_letnego_yubileya_vystavki</ref>\n*October 2019 - With Two hundred drones [https://www.dronisos.com Dronisos] presented the new Peugeot 208 above Paris.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/peugeotfr/status/1180926476243353602|title=La Nouvelle Peugeot208 se d\u00e9voile dans le ciel de Paris avec un show de drones in\u00e9dit en France.|date=6 October 2019|publisher=Peugeot France, Twitter}}</ref>\n*December 10, 2019 - 150 Drones were used to show a spectacular dazzling display for the ending ceremony of South Asian Games 2020, Nepal held at the Dasharath stadium in Kathmandu, Nepal.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Aerial advertising]]\n*[[Laser lighting display]]\n*[[Light art]]\n*[[Swarm robotics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Branches of the visual arts}}\n{{Robotics}}\n{{emerging technologies|displays=yes}}\n{{Display technology}}\n\n[[Category:Multi-robot systems]]\n[[Category:Emerging technologies]]\n[[Category:Light art]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Intel-Drone-100-Light-Show-980x653.jpg|thumb|\"Drone100\" performed by Ars Electronica Futurelab, for Intel, in 2015]]\nA '''drone display''' is the use of multiple [[unmanned aerial vehicle]]s (drones), often [[quadcopters]], flying in a coordinated fashion for public display. They are usually equipped with [[LED]]s, and the display held at night. The first Drone Display was presented in 2012 in Linz/Austria, where the Ars Electronica Futurelab introduced [[Ars Electronica#SPAXELS|Spaxels]] for the first time. The displays may be for entertainment, where the drones may use [[Flocking (behavior)|flocking]] or [[Swarm robotics|swarming behaviour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/studio-drift-franchise-freedom-smart-creativity/index.html|title=Swarm of drones illuminates the night sky|date=17 September 2018|publisher=}}</ref> The drones may also be coordinated to produce images. Using this [[emerging technology]], displays have been employed for advertising purposes as well.\n\n[[Intel]] has produced the [[Shooting Star (drone)|Shooting Star]], a type of drone used in light shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newsroom.intel.com/news/intel-celebrates-lgbtq-pride-2018-drone-light-show/|title=Intel Celebrates LGBTQ Pride 2018 with Drone Light Show - Intel Newsroom|publisher=}}</ref> They were used during the 2018 Winter Olympics, a Super Bowl halftime show in 2017, and a 2018 4 July celebration.<ref name=\"wired.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/story/more-inclusive-fourth-of-july-drone-show/|title=A Fourth of July Drone Show Helps Military Families With Special Needs|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nDrone light shows differ from fireworks displays in that drones are reusable, and do not produce air and noise pollution.<ref name=\"wired.com\"/> However, drone displays cannot take place during rain or strong winds.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/local/wisconsin/2018/07/27/drone-light-show-lights-up-evening-air-show-oshkosh/845104002/|title=Lighted drone show sparkles and wows crowd at EAA AirVenture|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==List of drone displays==\n*September 2012 - 49 LED-Equipped UAVs, called [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] (short for \"Space Elements\") have been shown at this [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ShGl5rQK3ew&list=PLKrmQr-thTw5kB1sqiEf4_XihIGfbB8XG&index=11 world premiere] by [[Ars Electronica]] [https://ars.electronica.art/futurelab/en/ Futurelab]\n*March 2013 - 50 [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] have been used to perform the Movie Premiere \"Startrek, Into Darkness\" next to Tower Bridge in London.\n*August 2013 - 30 [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] have been used to perform the [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NCOubOVh-yg&list=PLKrmQr-thTw5kB1sqiEf4_XihIGfbB8XG&index=12 opening of the new campus] at QUT, Brisbane / Australia.\n*November 2015 - 100 [http://www.spaxels.at SPAXELS] were used for the first [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]] [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nTwX1Z68qMY&list=PLKrmQr-thTw5kB1sqiEf4_XihIGfbB8XG&index=4 \"Drone100\"] by Ars Electronica Futurelab for Intel.  \n*November 2016 - Five hundred drones were used in Krailling, Germany, a [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]].\n*2017 - Three hundred drones performed during a [[Lady Gaga]] song in the [[Super Bowl LI halftime show]].\n*2017 - At the Fortune Global Forum in China, 1,180 drones performed.\n*September 2017 - To mark the release of the home version of the Wonder Woman film, 300 drones displayed an enormous \"W\" in the night sky above Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/tech/2017/09/19/drones-put-on-stunning-wonder-woman-display.html|title=Drones put on stunning 'Wonder Woman' display|first=Chris|last=Ciaccia|date=19 September 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n*December 2017 -  A swarm of 300 drones performed at [[Art Basel]] in [[Miami Beach]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nltimes.nl/2017/12/14/dutch-artists-fly-300-drone-starlings-swarm-miami|title=Dutch artists fly 300-drone \"starlings\" swarm in Miami|date=14 December 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n*2018 - During the [[2018 Winter Olympics opening ceremony]], 1,218 drones performed, breaking the previous world record.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/olympics-opening-ceremony-drone-show/|title=Inside the Olympics Opening Ceremony World-Record Drone Show|work=WIRED|access-date=2018-02-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n*June 2018 - One hundred drones performed in [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]], England, making shapes to music at the opening of the Great Exhibition of the North.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dezeen.com/2018/06/30/swarm-drones-perform-opening-great-exhibition-north-technology/ |title=Swarm of drones perform at the opening of the Great Exhibition of the North |publisher=Dezeen.com |date=2018-06-30 |accessdate=2018-09-18}}</ref>\n*July 2018 - Intel celebrates 50th anniversary with 2018 simultaneous drones over facility in Folsom, California, for Guinness world record.<ref>{{cite web |title=Intel Breaks Guinness World Records Title for Drone Light Shows in Celebration of 50th Anniversary |url=https://newsroom.intel.com/news/intel-breaks-guinness-world-records-title-drone-light-shows-celebration-50th-anniversary |website=News Byte |publisher=Intel Corporation |accessdate=August 2, 2019}}</ref>  Guinness credited Intel with flying 2066 simultaneous drones.<ref>{{cite web |title=Most Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs) airborne simultaneously |url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/373319-most%C2%A0unmanned-aerial%C2%A0vehicles%C2%A0uavs-airborne%C2%A0simultaneously%C2%A05-kg-or-less/ |website=Guinness World Records |publisher=Guinness World Records Limited |accessdate=August 2, 2019}}</ref>\n*January 2019 - Two hundred drones deployed the World's first New Year's Countdown set to fireworks and music for the New Year Celebrations on Al Marjan Island.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://skymagic.show/journal/al-marjan-island/|title=New Year Drone Show Celebrations|first=Emily|last=Wallace|date=28 February 2019|publisher=Skymagic}}</ref>\n*July 2019 - Two hundred and fifty drones performed at the opening show of the 24th World Scout Jamboree.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.2019wsj.org/opening-ceremony-drones/|title=Opening Ceremony Drones|date=29 July 2019|publisher=New World 19, LLC}}</ref>\n*August 2019 - Five hundred drones performed at the 80 years of VDNH celebration in Moscow<ref>https://www.1tv.ru/news/2019-08-04/369828-potryasayuschey_krasoty_shou_dronov_proshlo_na_vdnh_v_chest_80_letnego_yubileya_vystavki</ref>\n*October 2019 - Two hundred drones presented the new Peugeot 208 above Paris.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/peugeotfr/status/1180926476243353602|title=La Nouvelle Peugeot208 se d\u00e9voile dans le ciel de Paris avec un show de drones in\u00e9dit en France.|date=6 October 2019|publisher=Peugeot France, Twitter}}</ref>\n*December 10, 2019 - 150 Drones were used to show a spectacular dazzling display for the ending ceremony of South Asian Games 2020, Nepal held at the Dasharath stadium in Kathmandu, Nepal.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Aerial advertising]]\n*[[Laser lighting display]]\n*[[Light art]]\n*[[Swarm robotics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Branches of the visual arts}}\n{{Robotics}}\n{{emerging technologies|displays=yes}}\n{{Display technology}}\n\n[[Category:Multi-robot systems]]\n[[Category:Emerging technologies]]\n[[Category:Light art]]\n", "name_user": "Jdlauwereins", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eList of drone displays:Added a link to Dronisos who provided the drone show for the Peugeot 208 in Paris. Ref: Dronisos is credited in the Peugeot video linked to the page at Time=6 sec (left bottom corner)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drone_display"}
{"title_page": "Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production", "text_new": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = [[Annie Awards|Annie Award]] for Best Animated Television Production\n| description    = Excellence in [[television]] [[animation]]\n| presenter      = [[ASIFA-Hollywood]]\n| country        = United States\n| year           = 1992\n| year2          = \n| holder         = ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'' (general)<br>''[[Hilda (TV series)|Hilda]]'' (children)<br>''[[Ask the StoryBots]]'' (preschool)\n| website        = {{url|http://annieawards.org}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production''' is an [[Annie Awards|Annie Award]], awarded annually to the best animated television show. In 1998, the award was split into two categories, '''Outstanding Achievement in an Animated Daytime Television Program''' and '''Outstanding Achievement in an Animated Primetime or Late Night Television Program''', but was eventually combined into one category again. In 2008, the award received an offshoot category, the '''Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production for Children'''. This category will be listed here until it becomes a permanent establishment.<ref name=\"AnnieHistory\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/legacy.html|title=Annie Awards: Legacy|publisher=[[ASIFA-Hollywood]]|accessdate=2008-11-01| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081201083602/http://annieawards.org/legacy.html| archivedate= 1 December 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"23rdWinners\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/23rdwinners.html |title=23rd Annual Annie Awards - Winners |publisher=[[ASIFA-Hollywood]] |accessdate=2008-11-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218095653/http://annieawards.org/23rdwinners.html |archivedate=18 December 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Winners==\n\n===1990s===\n* '''1992 ([[20th Annie Awards|20th]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 [[20th Century Fox|Fox]]'''\n** ''[[TaleSpin]]'' \u2013 [[Disney Television Animation|Walt Disney Television Animation]]\n** ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show]]'' \u2013 [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]]\n** ''[[Darkwing Duck]]'' \u2013 Walt Disney Television Animation\n** ''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]'' \u2013 [[Amblin]]/[[Warner Bros. Television]]\n* '''1993 ([[21st Annie Awards|21st]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 [[20th Century Fox Television]]'''\n** ''[[The Little Mermaid (TV series)|The Little Mermaid]]'' \u2013 Walt Disney Television Animation\n** ''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]'' \u2013 [[Warner Bros. Animation]]\n** ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show]]'' \u2013 Nickelodeon\n** ''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n* '''1994 ([[22nd Annie Awards|22nd]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 Fox Television, [[Gracie Films]], [[Film Roman]]'''\n** ''[[Animaniacs]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Television Animation\n** ''[[The Critic]]'' \u2013 Gracie Films, Film Roman\n** ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show]]'' \u2013 Nickelodeon\n* '''1995 ([[23rd Annie Awards|23rd]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 Gracie Films, Film Roman'''\n** ''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[Animaniacs]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[The Maxx]]'' \u2013 [[MTV Animation]], [[Rough Draft Studios]]\n** ''[[The Tick]]'' \u2013 [[Sunbow Productions]], [[Graz Entertainment]]\n* '''1996 ([[24th Annie Awards|24th]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 20th Century Fox Television'''\n** ''[[Animaniacs]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[Gargoyles (TV show)|Gargoyles]]'' \u2013 Walt Disney Television Animation\n* '''1997 ([[25th Annie Awards|25th]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 20th Century Fox, Film Roman Productions, Gracie Films, [[Klasky Csupo]]'''\n** ''[[Dexter's Laboratory]]''\n** ''[[King of the Hill]]'' \u2013 20th Century Fox, Film Roman Productions\n** ''[[Pinky and the Brain]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros., Warner Bros. Animation, Amblin Entertainment\n** ''[[The Tick]]'' \