* [[Primetime Emmy Award for Short-Format Animation]]\n* [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Animated Series]]\n* [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Animated Program]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://annieawards.org/legacy/ Annie Awards: Legacy]\n\n{{Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production}}\n{{AnnieAwards}}\n\n[[Category:Annie Awards]]\n[[Category:American television awards]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1992]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = [[Annie Awards|Annie Award]] for Best Animated Television Production\n| description    = Excellence in [[television]] [[animation]]\n| presenter      = [[ASIFA-Hollywood]]\n| country        = United States\n| year           = 1992\n| year2          = \n| holder         = ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'' (general)<br>''[[Hilda (TV series)|Hilda]]'' (children)<br>''[[Ask the StoryBots]]'' (preschool)\n| website        = {{url|http://annieawards.org}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production''' is an [[Annie Awards|Annie Award]], awarded annually to the best animated television show. In 1998, the award was split into two categories, '''Outstanding Achievement in an Animated Daytime Television Program''' and '''Outstanding Achievement in an Animated Primetime or Late Night Television Program''', but was eventually combined into one category again. In 2008, the award received an offshoot category, the '''Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production for Children'''. This category will be listed here until it becomes a permanent establishment.<ref name=\"AnnieHistory\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/legacy.html|title=Annie Awards: Legacy|publisher=[[ASIFA-Hollywood]]|accessdate=2008-11-01| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081201083602/http://annieawards.org/legacy.html| archivedate= 1 December 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"23rdWinners\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/23rdwinners.html |title=23rd Annual Annie Awards - Winners |publisher=[[ASIFA-Hollywood]] |accessdate=2008-11-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218095653/http://annieawards.org/23rdwinners.html |archivedate=18 December 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Winners==\n\n===1990s===\n* '''1992 ([[20th Annie Awards|20th]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 [[20th Century Fox|Fox]]'''\n** ''[[TaleSpin]]'' \u2013 [[Disney Television Animation|Walt Disney Television Animation]]\n** ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show]]'' \u2013 [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]]\n** ''[[Darkwing Duck]]'' \u2013 Walt Disney Television Animation\n** ''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]'' \u2013 [[Amblin]]/[[Warner Bros. Television]]\n* '''1993 ([[21st Annie Awards|21st]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 [[20th Century Fox Television]]'''\n** ''[[The Little Mermaid (TV series)|The Little Mermaid]]'' \u2013 Walt Disney Television Animation\n** ''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]'' \u2013 [[Warner Bros. Animation]]\n** ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show]]'' \u2013 Nickelodeon\n** ''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n* '''1994 ([[22nd Annie Awards|22nd]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 Fox Television, [[Gracie Films]], [[Film Roman]]'''\n** ''[[Animaniacs]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Television Animation\n** ''[[The Critic]]'' \u2013 Gracie Films, Film Roman\n** ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show]]'' \u2013 Nickelodeon\n* '''1995 ([[23rd Annie Awards|23rd]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 Gracie Films, Film Roman'''\n** ''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[Animaniacs]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros. Animation\n** ''[[The Maxx]]'' \u2013 [[MTV Animation]], [[Rough Draft Studios]]\n** ''[[The Tick]]'' \u2013 [[Sunbow Productions]], [[Graz Entertainment]]\n* '''1996 ([[24th Annie Awards|24th]]) ''[[The Simpsons]]'' \u2013 20th Century Fox Television'''\n** ''[[Animaniacs]]'' \u2013 Warner Bros.