on\n  |votes      = 542\n  |percentage = 0.84\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 8,447\n  |percentage = 13.01\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = \n  |percentage = 75.66\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |swing      = \n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Elections in the 1960s===\n{{Election box begin |\n  |title=[[1966 United Kingdom general election|General election 1966]]: South West Hertfordshire\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Gilbert Longden]]\n  |votes      = 28,378\n  |percentage = 45.66\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = S. John Chapman\n  |votes      = 25,186\n  |percentage = 40.52\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Peter A.S. Benton\n  |votes      = 8,590\n  |percentage = 13.82\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 3,192\n  |percentage = 5.14\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = \n  |percentage = 83.12\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n  |winner     = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |swing      = \n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n{{Election box begin |\n  |title=[[1964 United Kingdom general election|General election 1964]]: South West Hertfordshire\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Gilbert Longden]]\n  |votes      = 28,308\n  |percentage = 45.77\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Syd Bidwell]]\n  |votes      = 22,237\n  |percentage = 35.96\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = R. 